# 9. Expected Benefits

The proposed PINN formulation is expected to provide several advantages over the baseline neural network.

## Improved Physical Consistency

Predictions are encouraged to obey aerodynamic relationships rather than merely fitting data.

---

## Better Generalization

Physics constraints act as regularization, potentially improving performance on unseen operating conditions.

---

## Improved Cp Predictions

The smoothness constraint may reduce unrealistic oscillations in pressure distributions.

---

## Enhanced Interpretability

Physical losses provide insight into whether model predictions satisfy known aerodynamic principles.

---

# 10. Limitations

Several limitations remain.

### Absence of Flow-Field Data

The dataset lacks velocity and pressure fields on CFD meshes.

Therefore:

- Full Navier-Stokes residuals cannot be enforced.
- The model is not a classical CFD PINN.

---

### Approximate Physics

Lift consistency is implemented through surrogate approximations rather than exact aerodynamic integration.

---

### Empirical Loss Weights

Physics-loss coefficients require tuning and may influence convergence behavior.

